Central Coffee Company is a family-owned and operated coffee shop in Charlotte, North Carolina. They first opened their shop in Plaza Midwood in May of 2009.  Their main goal is to serve remarkable coffee and fresh food products,   creating an inclusive community atmosphere. They believe that community is so important. Their staff and customers have become not just a community but their family and friends. They serve coffee roasted by Joe Van Gogh Coffee Roasters, located in Hillsborough, North Carolina, Joe Van Gogh has placed a lot of emphasis on social, economic, and environmentally responsible ways of producing their roasted coffees. The owners have been to Nicaragua with the company to develop their knowledge of the coffee industry and to learn where the beans come from and to appreciate the process from seed to plant to flower to tree to roasted coffee.

This is my absolute favorite coffee shop. Before the world shut down I visited Central Coffee every Sunday with my family after church. I also went there when I needed to do research and enjoyed the coffee and atmosphere very much. I often met friends there and told many people how much I loved Central. They have great coffee, great staff and a fabulous rewards program. I earned many free cups of coffee. When the pandemic hit and they were shut down I really missed the wonderful coffee but found I could order it and have it delivered. Ever since I have enjoyed Central coffee at home and brew the dark roast most mornings. Once they reopened I have been using the Odeko app to order my coffee every Sunday. It is a pretty easy app to use and I can order it ahead of time and by the time I drive to pick up my coffee it is ready fairly quickly. Today I did just that and ended up waiting for over 30 minutes. Customers who came after I arrived and ordered their coffee in person walked out with their cup of joes and I was still standing there waiting. I was livid. I never write reviews but I needed to get this off my chest. I'd like to say I am never going back but I know that isn't the case. I just wish they could have a better system right now.  They also claim to be short staffed which I find hard to believe with the amount of people out of work. Come on CC you can do better!

Great little spot for great coffee. Atmosphere is great if you are alone and want to get some work done-- if you can find a seat. Not great for having a meeting. Small narrow seating area with all hard reflective surfaces makes it difficult to talk quietly enough to be private. The central shorty is tasty and the homemade baklava is wonderful.
Good coffee and relaxing atmosphere. Can be pretty busy at times when it comes to seating thus they have the option to share a table with a stranger. Nice touch.
Love it. Great atmosphere, good coffee. Like the off-the-beaten path location.
